Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2015 15:32:03 +0200
Subject: vhost: actually track log eventfd file
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Git-commit: 7932c0bd7740f4cd2aa168d3ce0199e7af7d72d5
Patch-mainline: v4.2-rc5
References: bsc#942367, CVE-2015-6252

While reviewing vhost log code, I found out that log_file is never
set. Note: I haven't tested the change (QEMU doesn't use LOG_FD yet).

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Marc-Andr√© Lureau <marcandre.lureau@redhat.com>
Signed-off-by: Michael S. Tsirkin <mst@redhat.com>
Acked-by: Borislav Petkov <bp@suse.de>
---
 drivers/vhost/vhost.c |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

--- a/drivers/vhost/vhost.c
+++ b/drivers/vhost/vhost.c
@@ -847,6 +847,7 @@ long vhost_dev_ioctl(struct vhost_dev *d
 		}
 		if (eventfp != d->log_file) {
 			filep = d->log_file;
+			d->log_file = eventfp;
 			ctx = d->log_ctx;
 			d->log_ctx = eventfp ?
 				eventfd_ctx_fileget(eventfp) : NULL;
